IS  - 2
SP  - 179
EP  - 201
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/06/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-405X(80)90016-1
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304405X80900161
AB  - This paper reexamines the anomalous evidence concerning the efficiency of the listed options exchanges. We focus on the structure of trading costs in that market, and note several costs which generally have been ignored, the largest of which is the bid-ask spread. When we adjust the published trading rules for our estimates of these trading costs, the reported abnormal returns are eliminated.
